excerpt: Whimsical museum featuring scenes & characters from Hollywood movies, plus cars, tanks & mopeds.
detail_description: Museum Angkut is a unique and whimsical museum that showcases various types of transportation, from traditional to modern. It features scenes and characters from Hollywood movies, as well as an impressive collection of cars, tanks, and mopeds. The museum offers visitors the opportunity to explore the history of transportation through interactive displays and simulations. With almost 4 hectares of space, it is the first transportation museum in Southeast Asia.
name: Museum Angkut
address: Jl. Terusan Sultan Agung No.2, Ngaglik, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65314, Indonesia

excerpt: Amusement park operating at night with rides, live shows, carnival games & a market.
detail_description: Batu Night Spectacular (BNS) is a captivating night theme park located in Batu city, nestled on the hillside of Mount Panderman. The park offers a range of attractions including 35 exciting rides like the Sepeda Udara (Air Bike), live shows, carnival games, and a vibrant market.
name: Batu Night Spectacular (BNS)
address: Jl. Hayam Wuruk No.1, Oro-Oro Ombo, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65316, Indonesia

detail_description: Located near Jatim Park 2, Batu Secret Zoo is a modern zoo that offers an educational and enjoyable experience for children. It features a wide variety of animals from different parts of the world, including domestic and foreign species. The zoo is open every day from 10 am to 6 pm, with admission fees varying on weekdays and weekends. Visitors can expect spacious and clean facilities, as well as the opportunity to feed lions and bears for a small fee.
name: Batu Secret Zoo
address: Jl. Raya Oro-Oro Ombo No.9, Temas, Kec. Batu, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur, Indonesia

excerpt: Theme park with educational activities centered around natural history & biology, including a zoo.
detail_description: Jawa Timur Park 2, also known as East Java Park 2 in Batu Malang, is a modern and popular tourist destination that offers a unique blend of entertainment and education. The park features an animal park with various collections of animals, including monkeys, snakes, birds, seals, and camels. Visitors can explore the Museum Satwa to learn about extinct animals and view fossils of prehistoric creatures.
name: Jawa Timur Park 2
address: Jl. Raya Oro-Oro Ombo No.9, Temas, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65315, Indonesia

excerpt: Popular amusement park with a dinosaur attraction, wax museum, concessions & technology exhibits.
detail_description: Jawa Timur Park 3 is an impressive and ambitious amusement park located in the East Java region. It features more than eight themed areas, including dinosaur attractions, a wax museum, concessions, and technology exhibits. The park has implemented strict safety protocols amid the pandemic, including disinfecting rides after each use and checking visitors' temperatures before entry. Furthermore, guests must scan Peduli Lindungi codes to gain access to the park.
name: Jawa Timur Park 3
address: Jl. Ir. Soekarno No.144, Beji, Junrejo, Batu City, East Java 65236, Indonesia

excerpt: Theme park featuring rides, a food court & exhibits/ performances of traditional Indonesian culture.
detail_description: Jawa Timur Park 1 is a sprawling theme park that offers a wide range of attractions and activities for visitors of all ages. From thrilling roller coasters to interactive science exhibits, the park has something for everyone. It features more than 60 rides, including five roller coasters, making it the only theme park in Indonesia with such an offering.
name: Jawa Timur Park 1
address: Jl. Kartika No.2, Sisir, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65315, Indonesia

excerpt: Photography is popular at this famed “upside-down house” with food & a gift shop.
detail_description: Eco Green Park, located in East Java, is a unique ecological tour park designed to resemble a quaint village. It offers over 35 educational areas focused on environmental conservation and animal love. Visitors can explore various attractions such as the 'upside-down house,' Reptile Garden, Aquarium, Savannah, African Market, Elephant Ride area, Fantasy Land, swimming pool, New Safari, Exploration Continent and Stone ATV Adventure Land.
name: Eco Active Park
address: Jl. Raya Oro-Oro Ombo No.9A, Sisir, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65314, Indonesia

excerpt: Educational theme park with a dinosaur museum, interactive rides & photo ops, plus kids' events.
detail_description: Dino Park Jawa Timur Park 3, located in Batu, East Java, is an educational theme park that offers a combination of learning and entertainment. It is part of the larger amusement park complex known as Jawa Timur Park. The park features a dinosaur museum, interactive rides, photo opportunities, and events for kids. Visitors can explore the compact park on foot or rent electric bicycles to navigate the high ground areas.
name: Dino Park Jawa Timur Park 3
address: Jl. Ir. Soekarno No.112, Beji, Junrejo, Batu City, East Java 65236, Indonesia

excerpt: Popular amusement park with a dinosaur attraction, wax museum, concessions & technology exhibits.
name: Jawa Timur Park 3
address: Jl. Ir. Soekarno No.144, Beji, Junrejo, Batu City, East Java 65236, Indonesia

detail_description: Tirta Nirwana Songgoriti is a recreational park situated in the village of Songgokerto in Batu district. Positioned on Mount Panderman's slope, this park offers a hot spring pool where visitors can relax and enjoy the therapeutic benefits. The swimming facilities are immaculate and well-maintained, featuring separate areas for children with a playground and adults with ample seating for parents to supervise their kids.
name: Tirta Nirwana Songgoriti
address: Jl. Arumdalu No.1, Songgokerto, Kec. Batu, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65312, Indonesia

name: Museum Musik Dunia Jawa Timur Park 3
address: Lt. 1 Dino Mall, Jl. Ir. Soekarno No.144, Beji, Kec. Junrejo, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65236, Indonesia

excerpt: Open-air park showcasing jungle animals, art from recycled materials, a safari ride & bird shows.
name: Jungle Adventure
address: ECO GREEN PARK, Jl. Raya Oro-Oro Ombo, Temas, Kec. Batu, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65316, Indonesia

excerpt: This amusement park features water slides, paddle boats, a sky bike, gardens, a cinema & more.
detail_description: Selecta Recreational Park offers a variety of activities, including water slides, paddle boats, gardens and cinema. Entrance tickets can be purchased for Rp40.000/pax at the front gate and parking fees are Rp10.000/car. The park is quite spacious and has swimming pools with slides along with various restaurants. Visitors can stroll through the flower fields or take pictures among the blossoms, while others may opt to ride on the sky bike to view them from above.
name: Selecta Recreation Park
address: Jl. Raya Selecta No.1, Tulungrejo, Bumiaji, Batu City, East Java 65336, Indonesia

excerpt: Museum featuring a prehistoric animal diorama, life-size dinosaur replicas & educational exhibits.
detail_description: Museum Satwa is a fascinating attraction located within Jatim Park 2. It features lifelike dioramas of prehistoric animals, educational exhibits, and life-size replicas of dinosaurs. The museum offers an immersive experience with different backgrounds for each animal, allowing visitors to understand their natural habitats. It's a great place for both kids and adults to learn about various animals and insects through the detailed displays.
name: Museum Satwa
address: Jl. Raya Oro-Oro Ombo No.9, Temas, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65314, Indonesia

excerpt: Interactive museum featuring educational exhibits about the parts & functions of the human body.
detail_description: The Bagong Adventure Museum Tubuh is a science museum that covers the human body in great detail. The interactive exhibits teach visitors about the parts and functions of the body. There is also a cadaver on display which is an interesting addition.
name: The Bagong Adventure Museum Tubuh
address: Jl. Kartika No.2, Sisir, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65314, Indonesia

excerpt: Reptile-themed amusement park with educational exhibits & shows, rides & pools with water slides.
detail_description: Predator Fun Park is an amusement park with a reptile theme that offers educational exhibits, shows, and various rides including pools equipped with water slides. Visitors can observe different types of reptiles such as crocodiles, snakes, and iguanas. The park also features beautiful photo spots and art designs for photography enthusiasts to capture memories. In addition to crocodile statues, the park houses other animals like donkeys, large mice and fishes.
name: Batu Ekonomis Park (BEP)
address: Jl. Raya Tlekung No.315, Tlekung, Junrejo, Batu City, East Java 65327, Indonesia

excerpt: Waterfall cascading over boulders through forest to a plunge pool with a steep path & camping area.
detail_description: Coban Talun Waterfall is a highly recommended destination for those seeking to rejuvenate their mind and body. The waterfall flows gracefully over rocks amidst lush greenery, culminating in a plunge pool that visitors can swim in. The area also boasts several attractions such as a hydrangea plantation with vibrant flowers and campsites including Apache camp and pagupon camp, where visitors can indulge in outdoor activities with friends or family.
name: Coban Talun Waterfall
address: Tulungrejo, Bumiaji, Batu City, East Java, Indonesia

excerpt: This family-friendly educational park allows children to interact with rabbits & has a cafe.
detail_description: Rabbit Park is a family-oriented educational park that provides an opportunity for children to interact with rabbits. The park also features a cafe where visitors can enjoy refreshments. For those who love bunnies, Rabbit Park is the perfect place to visit as it offers plenty of opportunities to see and interact with these furry creatures. However, be cautious of bunny satay restaurants along the way that might not be appropriate for young children.
name: Rabbit Park
address: Samaan Klojen, Jurangrejo, Pandesari, Kec. Pujon, Kabupaten Malang, Jawa Timur 65112, Indonesia

name: Batu Flower Garden (wisata)
address: Unnamed Road, Oro-Oro Ombo, Kec. Batu, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65316, Indonesia

excerpt: Popular spot for selfies amid an array of whimsical sculptures in front of extensive views.
detail_description: Taman Langit Gunung Banyak is a renowned tourist spot with a plethora of quirky sculptures and breathtaking scenery. Visitors can capture stunning selfies while exploring the whimsical art installations amidst the vast mountainous backdrop. The attraction offers an extensive range of charming sculptures, providing tourists with countless photo opportunities in one location. This picturesque spot is perfect for those seeking an escape from busy city life and immersing themselves in nature's beauty.
name: Taman Langit Gunung Banyak
address: Jl. Gn. Banyak, Gunungsari, Bumiaji, Batu City, East Java 65312, Indonesia

detail_description: If you love beautiful landscapes and hospitable people, you will love the Wisata Desa Agro Bumiaji orchard. This is a stunning spot with rolling hills and dense forests, perfect for a picnic or a stroll. The fruit here is also some of the best in the region, so be sure to try some of their delicious treats!
name: Wisata Desa Agro Bumiaji
address: 4GRQ+M49, Jl. Kastubi, Bumiaji, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65331, Indonesia

excerpt: Mountain peak & hiking spot with walking trails, lush foliage & scenic panoramas from the summit.
detail_description: Panderman Mountain is a scenic and picturesque peak that serves as both a hiking spot and a destination for nature enthusiasts. It boasts well-defined walking trails, abundant greenery, and breathtaking panoramic views from its summit. While not excessively challenging, it offers an exhilarating experience for new hikers. It is advisable to embark on the hike in the early evening to make the most of daylight hours, as well as to witness a captivating sunrise.
name: Panderman Mountain
address: Kehutanan, Batu, Batu City, East Java, Indonesia

excerpt: Rural educational farm keeping cows & livestock with adventure play equipment for children.
detail_description: Kampung Sapi Adventure is a tourist attraction in the Malaysian state of Sarawak that features rural educational farm keeping cows and livestock with adventure play equipment for children. The attractions has great views, a cozy garden, and fun for tourists.
name: Kampung Sapi Adventure
address: Gg. 1, Beji, Junrejo, Batu City, East Java 65236, Indonesia

excerpt: Walks to a cave on a cliffside trail with quirky landscaped photo backdrops & wood sculptures.
detail_description: Goa Pinus is a popular tourist attraction located on a cliffside trail. It features unique landscaped photo backdrops and wood sculptures, creating a quirky and artistic atmosphere. The area is close to the paragliding spot, providing cool air even during the hottest hours of the day. The ticket price is affordable, with 5k for entrance and an additional 5k for access to the photo shoot areas.
name: Goa Pinus
address: 5F2V+QJJ, Gg. Mbah Ba'i, Gunungsari, Bumiaji, Batu City, East Java 65391, Indonesia

detail_description: Omah Budaya Slamet Batu is not just a house, but also an art gallery owned by Mr. Hendrikus. The owner is intelligent and can engage in deep philosophical discussions. The residents of the house are extremely pleasant and provide impeccable hospitality. This gallery house offers a serene atmosphere, perfect for various activities or simply relaxation. Inside, you will come across numerous unique paintings of considerable size.
name: Omah Budaya Slamet Batu
address: Jl. Imam Bonjol No.90, Bumiaji, Batu City, East Java 65331, Indonesia

excerpt: Easily accessible natural waterfall with tropical scenery, benches for picnics & bike rentals.
detail_description: Nestled in the lush landscapes of Pujon, Coban Rondo Waterfall is a delightful natural gem that offers visitors an easy escape into nature. Accessible by car, it's just a short 100-meter stroll from the parking area to the waterfall itself. While not particularly large, its charm lies in the refreshing mist and cool air that envelops you as you approach.
name: Coban Rondo Waterfall Pujon
address: Sebaluh Jl. Coban Rondo No.RT.30, Krajan, Pandesari, Pujon, Malang Regency, East Java 65391, Indonesia

detail_description: Songgoriti Hot Spring is a must-visit destination in Batu, offering a serene escape into nature. Surrounded by breathtaking scenery, this natural hot spring provides both cold and hot pools for relaxation. The area also features a sound system and occasional traditional dance shows, adding to the overall experience. Visitors can enjoy delicious food and beverages while taking in the stunning views of the mountains. Additionally, the friendly staff ensures that guests feel well taken care of without being pushy.
name: Songgoriti Hot Spring
address: 4FMR+9MC, Jl. Raya Songgoriti No.31, Songgokerto, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65312, Indonesia

detail_description: "Dunia tanpa gadget playground" is a thrilling and comprehensive children's play area that offers a comfortable environment for kids to have fun.
name: Dunia tanpa gadget playground
address: 4GHM+FR8, Jl. Sultan Hasan Jl. Sutan Hasan Halim, Temas, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65315, Indonesia

detail_description: CIRCUS MAGIC is a mesmerizing and enchanting experience that combines the thrill of a circus with the wonder of magic. The show features astonishing illusions, mind-boggling acts, and captivating performances that will leave you in awe. With a blend of acrobatics, comedy, and spellbinding tricks, CIRCUS MAGIC offers an unforgettable spectacle for audiences of all ages.
name: CIRCUS MAGIC
address: Jl. Ir. Soekarno No.144, Beji, Kec. Junrejo, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65236, Indonesia

detail_description: To grasp the severity of Soeharto's reign, it is imperative to visit Museum HAM Omah Munir, an establishment that commemorates the atrocities of The New Order Regime. Here, one can comprehend the valiant struggles undertaken by Mr. Munir and his counterparts in their fight against human rights violations. We must not overlook nor trivialize their selfless acts for the sake of present-day society. This museum serves as a poignant tribute to Mr.
name: Museum HAM Omah Munir
address: Jl. Bukit Berbunga No.2, Sidomulyo, Batu, Batu City, East Java 65317, Indonesia

excerpt: Photogenic theme park with floral displays, a topiary garden, a butterfly house & camel rides.
detail_description: Batu Love Garden, also known as BALOGA, is a picturesque theme park featuring stunning floral displays, a charming topiary garden, and a delightful butterfly house. Visitors can also enjoy camel rides and various family-friendly games. The park offers e-bike rentals for convenient exploration of its numerous attractions. With an array of photogenic spots and affordable food and beverage options, it's an ideal destination for families and individuals alike. For those seeking to avoid crowds, visiting on weekdays is recommended.
name: Batu Love Garden - BALOGA
address: Jl. Raya Pandanrejo No.91, Pandanrejo, Kec. Bumiaji, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65332, Indonesia

detail_description: If you're in the mood for fresh, succulent apples right from the orchard, Petik Apel Kebun 8 Kota Batu is the ideal destination. The staff are exceptionally friendly and helpful, providing a basket and explaining the pricing (20K per kilo for u-pick) as well as introducing various apple varieties on offer. The orchards themselves are breathtakingly beautiful; wandering through rows of trees and selecting the most appealing apples is an exhilarating experience.
name: Petik Apel Kebun 8 Kota Batu
address: Jl. Raya Sumber Brantas, Tulungrejo, Kec. Bumiaji, Kota Batu, Jawa Timur 65336, Indonesia
